'''''Monnechroma azureum''''' is a species of [[beetle]] in the family [[Cerambycidae]]. It was described by Demets in 1976.<ref>Bezark, Larry G. [http://plant.cdfa.ca.gov/byciddb/bycidview.asp A Photographic Catalog of the Cerambycidae of the World]. Retrieved on 22 May 2012.</ref> It is known from [[Mexico]] and [[Costa Rica]].

